===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=[[have]] [[eyes]] [[bigger]] [[than]] one's [[stomach]]|has eyes bigger than one's stomach|having eyes bigger than one's stomach|had eyes bigger than one's stomach}}

# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To [[take]] more [[food]] on one's plate than one can eat; to be [[greedy]].
#: ''He has '''eyes bigger than his stomach'''.''
#: ''You have '''eyes bigger than your stomach'''.''
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To want more than one can handle.
#* {{quote-book|title=Bookkeeping For Dummies|page=75|books.google.com/books?isbn=1742469973|author=Veechi Curtis, Lynley Averis|year=2010|passage=When choosing software, don't '''have eyes bigger than your stomach'''. Rather, stick to whatever level of software you need, and no more.}}

